.TH PRT-PRINTF 8 "prt-#VERSION# Manual"
.SH NAME
prt-printf \- Print formatted list of available packages
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B prt printf [--sort=\fIformat\fB] [--regex] [--filter=\fINAME\fB]
.I format
.SH DESCRIPTION
Print formatted list of available packages.
It looks in all directories specified in \fC/etc/prt.conf\fR.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-sort=\fIformat\fR
The \fIformat\fR string (see below) that is used to sort the output.
.TP
.B \-\-regex
Interpret filter argument as a regular expression.
.TP
.B \-\-filter=\fINAME\fR
Filter listing packages by name. The filter option argument may be the
string, wildcard or regex.
.TP
.I format
The string that contains variables, which are replaced like this:
.RS
.TP
%n
name
.TP
%p
path
.TP
%v
version
.TP
%r
release number
.TP
%d
description
.TP
%e
dependencies
.TP
%u
url
.TP
%P
packager
.TP
%M
maintainer
.TP
%R
has readme (yes/no)
.TP
%A
has pre-install script (yes/no)
.TP
%B
has post-install script (yes/no)
.TP
%C
has pre-remove script (yes/no)
.TP
%D
has post-remove script (yes/no)
.TP
%l
is locked (yes/no)
.TP
%i
is installed (yes/no/diff) where:
.RS
\'diff\' means the package is installed and different port version is
available in the ports tree.
.RE
.RE
